.TH "BATPIPE" 1
.SH NAME
batpipe - A \fR\fIless\fR (and \fR\fIbat\fR) preprocessor for viewing more types of files in the terminal.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.SH "USAGE"
.P
Like lesspipe, \fR\fIbatpipe\fR is designed to work with programs that support preprocessing with the \fR\fILESSOPEN\fR environment variable. Setting up \fR\fIbatpipe\fRwill depend on your shell:
.P
\fR\fBBash:\fR
.P
eval "$(batpipe)"
.P
\fR\fBFish:\fR
.P
eval (batpipe)
